agents.name: TimeBot
agents.description: TimeBot is an AI agent that tells the current time in the UK

agents.name: TimeBot USA
agents.description: TimeBot USA is an AI agent that reports the current time across various time zones in the USA.

example_queries.query: What is the current time in New York?
example_queries.response: The current time in New York is 3:00 PM EDT.

agents.name: TimeBot Asia
agents.description: TimeBot Asia is a specialized AI agent for providing current time in major Asian cities.

example_queries.response: The current time in Tokyo is 4:00 PM JST.

agents.name: TimeBot Europe
agents.description: TimeBot Europe helps users find the current time in various European cities.

example_queries.response: The current time in Paris is 10:00 AM CEST.

agents.name: TimeBot Australia
agents.description: TimeBot Australia is an AI agent dedicated to providing the current time in Australian regions.

example_queries.response: The current time in Sydney is 7:00 PM AEST.

agents.name: Mischievous TimeBot
agents.description: Mischievous TimeBot is a playful AI agent that intentionally tells the wrong time, adding a bit of humor and unpredictability.

example_queries.response: Sure, it's 3:15 PM right now, why not, that could be the time!

agents.name: Binary TimeBot
agents.description: Binary TimeBot is an AI agent that reports the current time in binary format, ideal for computer enthusiasts and coders.

example_queries.query: What is the current time in binary?

agents.name: EchoBot
agents.description: EchoBot is a simple AI agent designed to echo back whatever the user says, providing a mirror for communication and testing.

agents.name: MathBot
agents.description: MathBot is an AI agent adept at solving mathematical problems, from basic arithmetic to complex equations.

example_queries.query: What is the square root of 144?

agents.name: JokeBot V2
agents.description: JokeBot is a humor-oriented AI agent designed to generate and tell jokes, riddles, and humorous anecdotes.

example_queries.response: Why don't scientists trust atoms? Because they make up everything!
